      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_key_gen_1a02fd73d861ef2e4aabb38c0c9ff82947" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void init</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>init</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The init function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function checks if both TLS key files still exist. If yes the member variable keygen_done will be set to true. Aftwards the function checks if the &quot;key tranferred&quot; file exist and in this case it set member variable transfer_done. If key generation is still done, indicated by flag keygen_done the function returns immediately. <linebreak/>
If key generation is not done, the key generation will be initialized by call of the function mbedtls_ctr_drbg_init provided by mbedtls crypto library, which initializes the CTR_DRBG context and prepare it for seed generation. Afterwards the entropy controller device structure will be retrieved from device tree by calling macro DEVICE_DT_GET and the function checks if the device is ready for usage with call of function device_is_ready. If device is not ready a debug message at error level will be printed, otherwise seed will be generated by call of function mbedtls_ctr_drbg_seed, which also set up the CTR_DRBG entropy source for future reseeds. <linebreak/>
With call of the functions mbedtls_pk_init and mbedtls_pk_setup provided by the mbedtls crypto library the mbedTLS structure of type mbedtls_pk_context will be initialized. Calling function mbedtls_ecp_gen_key generates the TLS keypair. Calling function mbedtls_pk_write_key_pem extract the private key into a string, which will than be stored into file system. Calling function mbedtls_pk_write_key_pem extract the public key into a string, which will than also be stored into file system. Finally the called functions mbedtls_pk_free and mbedtls_ctr_drbg_free release the components of the context variables. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
